A CHARITY that offers support to the elderly wants to open a new group. Volunteers call for OAP party plan A CHARITY that offers support to the elderly wants to open a new group.Contact the Elderly provides monthly Sunday tea parties for people over 75 who are lonely or isolated.The charity is now hoping to start a new group in the Clydebank area.To volunteer to help contact Margaret Oliver via margaret.oliver@contact-the-elderly.org.uk or 01389 605915. 